tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1433:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/phase-events.jsonl:30:{"schema_version":"1.0.0","event_id":"019db58b-b0b7-7541-bceb-bef4f5409975","spec_id":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000c01","phase":"shape-spec","agent_session_id":"cli-session","timestamp":"2026-04-22T14:15:24.087286Z","origin_kind":"tool_primary","tool":"create_task","payload":{"event_type":"task_created","task":{"id":"019db58b-b0b7-7541-bceb-beefc3b8876c","spec_id":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000c01","title":"T02 Phase 0 Behavior Inventory And Traceability","description":"Define stable BEH-* IDs and map Phase 0 Feature 1.1-8.1 behaviors to executable scenario obligations (positive and falsification).","acceptance_criteria":[{"id":"t02-ac1","description":"Behavior map covers all in-scope Phase 0 behaviors.","measurable":"Traceability artifact lists behavior ID -> scenario ownership."},{"id":"t02-ac2","description":"Task closes with just check green and artifact validation.","measurable":"Artifact is linted/validated and just check succeeds."}],"origin":{"kind":"shape_spec"},"status":{"state":"pending"},"depends_on":["019db58b-b051-70e1-9190-c4f9cd09b5e7"],"parent_task_id":null,"created_at":"2026-04-22T14:15:24.087277Z","updated_at":"2026-04-22T14:15:24.087277Z"},"origin":{"kind":"shape_spec"}}}
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1671:        "body": "Behavior proof is expressed as executable `.feature` scenarios (cucumber-rs) tagged with a stable behavior ID (`@BEH-*`). Every in-scope behavior needs both a positive witness (scenario demonstrates the behavior) and a falsification witness (scenario demonstrates the inverse is rejected). Unit and integration tests via `nextest` remain in support of the scenario suite — they do not substitute for scenario ownership of a behavior ID."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1693:        "body": "Every testable behavior has a stable `BEH-*` identifier that is referenced from: (1) the spec/plan behavior inventory, (2) the cucumber scenario via a `@BEH-*` tag, (3) mutation survivor triage records, and (4) coverage classification records. Behavior IDs are immutable once published; renames require an abandon+replace event pair in the orchestrator. A behavior claim without a resolvable `BEH-*` link in all four artifacts is treated as incomplete traceability and fails the final gate."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1733:        "body": "Test suites are gated on mutation strength via `cargo-mutants`. Surviving mutants are treated as evidence of weak scenarios: each survivor must be triaged and resolved against a behavior ID (`BEH-*`) — either by tightening an existing scenario, adding a falsification scenario, or explicitly recording the mutant as equivalent with a linked justification. Mutation regressions fail the final gate; the staged `just` recipes surface mutant output in a machine-consumable form for triage."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:2061:      "description": "Define stable BEH-* IDs and map Phase 0 Feature 1.1-8.1 behaviors to executable scenario obligations (positive and falsification).",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:2210:      "title": "T07 Wave B Scenario Migration (Features 4-6)",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:2211:      "description": "Implement behavior scenarios for methodology boundary, task guard monotonicity, and typed tool-surface capability/transport parity behaviors.",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:2215:          "description": "Mapped Wave B behaviors have passing positive/falsification scenarios.",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:2216:          "measurable": "Feature 4-6 mappings resolve to passing scenario evidence."
