tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/027-harness_audit-task.log:5386:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/024-harness_do-task.log:874:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/002-harness_do-task.log:1132:tanren/standards/rust-testing/behavior-traceability.md:17:Every testable behavior has a stable `BEH-*` identifier that is referenced from: (1) the spec/plan behavior inventory, (2) the cucumber scenario via a `@BEH-*` tag, (3) mutation survivor triage records, and (4) coverage classification records. Behavior IDs are immutable once published; renames require an abandon+replace event pair in the orchestrator. A behavior claim without a resolvable `BEH-*` link in all four artifacts is treated as incomplete traceability and fails the final gate.
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/027-harness_audit-task.log:5387:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/024-harness_do-task.log:875:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/002-harness_do-task.log:1133:tanren/standards/rust-testing/bdd-scenarios.md:16:Behavior proof is expressed as executable `.feature` scenarios (cucumber-rs) tagged with a stable behavior ID (`@BEH-*`). Every in-scope behavior needs both a positive witness (scenario demonstrates the behavior) and a falsification witness (scenario demonstrates the inverse is rejected). Unit and integration tests via `nextest` remain in support of the scenario suite — they do not substitute for scenario ownership of a behavior ID.
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/027-harness_audit-task.log:5388:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/024-harness_do-task.log:876:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/002-harness_do-task.log:1134:tanren/standards/rust-testing/mutation-strength.md:15:Test suites are gated on mutation strength via `cargo-mutants`. Surviving mutants are treated as evidence of weak scenarios: each survivor must be triaged and resolved against a behavior ID (`BEH-*`) — either by tightening an existing scenario, adding a falsification scenario, or explicitly recording the mutant as equivalent with a linked justification. Mutation regressions fail the final gate; the staged `just` recipes surface mutant output in a machine-consumable form for triage.
