tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/027-harness_audit-task.log:5412:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/024-harness_do-task.log:900:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/002-harness_do-task.log:1221:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1671:        "body": "Behavior proof is expressed as executable `.feature` scenarios (cucumber-rs) tagged with a stable behavior ID (`@BEH-*`). Every in-scope behavior needs both a positive witness (scenario demonstrates the behavior) and a falsification witness (scenario demonstrates the inverse is rejected). Unit and integration tests via `nextest` remain in support of the scenario suite — they do not substitute for scenario ownership of a behavior ID."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/027-harness_audit-task.log:5413:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/024-harness_do-task.log:901:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/002-harness_do-task.log:1224:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1693:        "body": "Every testable behavior has a stable `BEH-*` identifier that is referenced from: (1) the spec/plan behavior inventory, (2) the cucumber scenario via a `@BEH-*` tag, (3) mutation survivor triage records, and (4) coverage classification records. Behavior IDs are immutable once published; renames require an abandon+replace event pair in the orchestrator. A behavior claim without a resolvable `BEH-*` link in all four artifacts is treated as incomplete traceability and fails the final gate."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/027-harness_audit-task.log:5414:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/024-harness_do-task.log:902:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/002-harness_do-task.log:1225:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1733:        "body": "Test suites are gated on mutation strength via `cargo-mutants`. Surviving mutants are treated as evidence of weak scenarios: each survivor must be triaged and resolved against a behavior ID (`BEH-*`) — either by tightening an existing scenario, adding a falsification scenario, or explicitly recording the mutant as equivalent with a linked justification. Mutation regressions fail the final gate; the staged `just` recipes surface mutant output in a machine-consumable form for triage."
